Control.CreateGraphics must be driver-routable.  The stock implementation calls
Graphics.FromHwnd directly, which hard-wires System.Drawing/libgdiplus to the
native HWND path and bypasses XplatUIDriver.  That breaks loadable backends whose
native handles are not libgdiplus HWNDs, such as a Wayland backend that paints
into managed SHM backbuffers.

Add an explicit virtual XplatUIDriver.CreateGraphics hook with the existing
Graphics.FromHwnd behavior as the default, then route Control.CreateGraphics
through XplatUI.  Existing backends keep the same behavior unless they override
the hook; non-HWND backends get a compile-time checked extension point instead
of reflection or backend-specific special cases in Control.

diff --git a/mcs/class/System.Windows.Forms/System.Windows.Forms/Control.cs b/mcs/class/System.Windows.Forms/System.Windows.Forms/Control.cs
index 5b1e913..7bd86de 100644
--- a/mcs/class/System.Windows.Forms/System.Windows.Forms/Control.cs
+++ b/mcs/class/System.Windows.Forms/System.Windows.Forms/Control.cs
@@ -3603,7 +3603,7 @@
 			if (!IsHandleCreated) {
 				this.CreateHandle();
 			}
-			return Graphics.FromHwnd(this.window.Handle);
+			return XplatUI.CreateGraphics (this.window.Handle);
 		}
 
 		public DragDropEffects DoDragDrop(object data, DragDropEffects allowedEffects) {
